elderly American lady, with pink and violetwrinkles and rufous hair: we kept alternately chatting, dozing and drinkingBloody Marshas, her joke--not appreciated by our sky-blue hostess. It wasdelightful to observe the amazement expressed by old Miss Havemeyer (herrather incredible name) when I told her that I had spurned the Intourist'soffer of a sightseeing tour of Leningrad; that I had not peeped into Lenin'sroom in the Smolny; had not visited one cathedral; had not eaten somethingcalled "tabak